hedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Aggro management</span><hr size=1> Several classes have spells to manage aggro -- it's actually one of the few things druids don't have in *any* degree. Enchanters are generally charged with the role of manipulating aggro, with their mem blur line and the &quot;visage&quot; line introduced with Luclin. <br>
<br>
My thought is that with chanters already performing specific roles in crowd control and buffs/debuffs/manatapping, it wouldn't step on their toes to give druids some specialist abilities in this area.<br>
<br>
What I'd like to see is a 50+ level line of druid spells similar to the chanter visage line. <br>
<br>
For instance:<br>
<br>
&quot;Shroud of Karana&quot; would envelop a single target in a veil of mist, hiding that person from the mob, effectively causing the mob to forget that person for a brief time. Excellent for protecting a caster or healer who happened to get too high on the mob's hate list, and allow MT a chance to build some aggro back up.<br>
<br>
&quot;Balance of Life&quot; would imbue a single melee groupmate with a strong irrestistable lifetap that would proc on every hit for one round. Would be useful for regaining aggro, fairly high recast time.<br>
<br>
&quot;Call of Savagery&quot; would cause a melee groupmate to land a Flurry of attacks for two rounds, similar to AA ability that warriors can get. Useful for building and regaining aggro.<br>
<br>
&quot;Harmony of the Grove&quot; would be somewhat like group foliage, but instead of making the group invisible, it would give each person a small radius of 'null' aggro for a fixed amount of time; I'd suggest 5 tics. Note that it would not reverse any existing aggro a character had with mob(s), therefore would be a short duration travel spell rather than for combat aggro. <br>
<br>
Not sure what to recommend for which of the 51-60 levels each of these spells would be gained, but I'd definitely propose that all of these spells would only be castable on players 51+ level. <br>
<br>
~Firemynd <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Might be Housebroken</span><br>  Posts: 290<br> <font color=#333399>(7/17/02 3:00:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro management</span><hr size=1> Actually...<br>
<br>
I think they should just make the spell casting subtlety aaxp skill available to the priest classes.<br>
<br>
Yes clerics have DA.  But we all know that heals are huge taunt, and we don't get an offset.<br>
<br>
I certainly would love that skill for druids.  It is strange to me that our nukes are pretty big (compared to mages and not too bad compared to wizards) and yet we don't have this skill.<br>
<br>
I would not want to take the visage roll from chanters.  They already tend to have little to do during the actual fight.  Most raid encounters are about fighting a single mob (ok not so on some of those Akheva bosses and some of the Ssra bosses, but you get the picture).  Yes they can get busy but generally it is enough to have Visage on the tank at the beginning of the fight.<br>
<br>
Chanters tend to get really, really bored most raids. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A> at: 7/17/02 3:02:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubernfizzlesticks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bern Fizzlesticks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#333399>(7/17/02 3:08:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro management</span><hr size=1> Nice ideas. Creative!<br>
<br>
How about making druids living focus items (this might be dull). Give us spells that extend buff duration or range or increase the damage or heal amounts of the target for a short duration. A buff that would cause tanks, healers or dd folks to crit for 10 seconds.  If we could improve other people's abilities you wouldn't just need one druid like you need low numbers of shamans.  <p>Bern Fizzlesticks <br>
-Bristlebane
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Might be Housebroken</span><br>  Posts: 293<br> <font color=#333399>(7/17/02 3:11:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro management</span><hr size=1> As a rule, buffing is a bad path to raid neededness.<br>
<br>
You usually can get by with 1 or 2 people buffing.  Debuffing you need on the fly and can / should spread to control agro so you want a few more.  Mana intensive buffs ok maybe 2 or possibly 3.<br>
<br>
But if our raid neededness were to center around buffs and buffs alone, it would simply mean 2box druids being parked at raid locs to refresh buffs, then camped out to not lag the raid.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubernfizzlesticks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bern Fizzlesticks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333399>(7/17/02 3:17:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro management</span><hr size=1> If any of the above buffs were short lived and needed on the spot. With aggro management druid would have to be paying attention to who next might be in danger and be a step ahead of the game to keep them safe. For focusy spells they would last for short times and would need to be refreshed. So you would see a bunch of druids running around getting all the tanks and clerics and wizards and other druids to improve their abilities and making them more mana efficient. Might be tedious however.  <p>Bern Fizzlesticks <br>
-Bristlebane
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufiremynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Firemynd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Just got my shots!</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#333399>(7/17/02 4:14:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro management</span><hr size=1> &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I would not want to take the visage roll from chanters. They already tend to have little to do during the actual fight. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
In that respect, playing a chanter can be much like playing a driud. If you make it a point to be aware of what's going on around you (not just in your group), you can find ways to benefit both raiding and grouping parties -- which to me, is why a 1box druid/chanter/shaman/cleric/etc will always be better than someone 2boxing it. Pre-fight buffing would be the only exception.<br>
<br>
I've seen several encounters succeed where a nasty wipeout seemed inevitable, because an alert chanter acted quickly. E.g. chain runing the cleric when the MT went down quicker than expected, or used a low level DD spell (w/stun) when they couldn't get close enough to use AE stuns. When playing my druid, I've saved many lives by having target hotkeys set for those most likely to draw aggro (especially chanters), as well as using /assist on mobs to monitor their hate lists.<br>
<br>
All I was proposing with the spells listed above, would be ways for druids to contribute to aggro management without relying solely upon our inferior healing ability to keep people alive in bad situations. Wouldn't be as necessary if VI would bring the druid more in line with other &quot;priest&quot; classes, but that's a different discussion entirely. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
~Firemynd <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showPrevMessage?topicID=30.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showNextMessage?topicID=30.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=5><img src=http://dev.thedruidsgrove.org/images/forum/addreplya.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.emailToFriend?topicID=30.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.threadControl?topicID=30.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=30.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=30.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests">Quests<option value="thedruidsgrovehuntingguide">Hunting Guide<option value="thedruidsgrovedruidicequipment">Druidic Equip